Rating: 4
This was fantastic. I read through some of the prior reviews and many doubled the tomatoes but didn't give a reason why. The dish makes its own liquid as it simmers while covered so there is no need for it unless you want a curry heavy on tomato flavor. I made a couple of changes: I used skinless thighs with bones (10 of them) and it took 40 minutes to cook. I also doubled the garlic and ginger. Lastly, I realized I only had fat free plain yogurt on hand so I used sour cream instead- no curdling issues like others had. Everything else I did as written. There was enough cayenne for a slight zing, however if you are adding in all sorts of extra liquids you will need to adjust accordingly. My suggestion to others would be use whatever chicken parts you want and double the ginger and garlic. I will make it again in the exact same manner!

