Rating: 4
This is a delicious curry. For a quicker version I sauteed onions, ginger, garlic, and spices (adding a teaspoon of sugar) in olive oil until softened. Then added thinly sliced chicken breast and sauteed until just cooked through. Removed cooked chicken from skillet. Added match stick sized chopped veggies to skillet and cooked until slightly softened. I used carrots, zucchini, red pepper, fresh chopped tomato, and small broccoli florets. Added 1/2 cup beef or chix broth and 3/4 cup coconut milk and a splash of fish sauce. Cooked until sauce thickened and returned chicken to skillet until heated through. Served over basmati rice and sprinkled with finely chopped cashews and cilantro. YUM!

