Rating: 4
This recipe has become a go-to for our household. Over time we've slightly modified it to suit our tastes in the following ways: (1) using fresh, instead of canned, tomatoes is much quicker and prevents any acidic, tinny taste too often accompanied by canned tomatoes and inadequate cooking time; (2) substituting cubed chicken breast for the mixed white and brown meats (reducing the cooking time to prevent drying); (3) adding either coconut milk in place of yogurt (as suggested by a previous reviewer, if I recall) or, when in a pinch, a few drops of coconut extract plus the yogurt the recipe calls for. The sweetness the coconut adds is too fantastic to miss. I've also found that any number of ground nuts will substitute nicely for cashews, if the larder so dictates.

