These reviews crack me up... I'm from India, so I have tasted and cooked some other curries before. But isn't that irrelevant ? To the point, I've made and tasted this recipe, which qualifies me to rate how much I like it. (And, I like it quite a bit! Not all curry powders are bad, you just have to use one that has the right spices for the meat you are using. (Fresh spice is always better but really, we don't all have time on a weeknight.) Just because it's not your naanii's best curry doesn't mean it can't be good. One small change: I only use thighs and drumsticks, so it was too oily. When the meat was done cooking (before adding yoghurt) I took out the chicken and chilled it and the sauce separately, and then skimmed the solidied fat off the top--I will save it to fry things. I reheated the chicken in the oven separately to make it more crispy, and the sauce still had plenty of fat left when reheated. My family loved this, and I plan to make it again! There are plenty good curries besides classic Indian ones--maybe this one can be a classic American curry.

