To .. A Cook... Perhaps you should re-read my review. I've been cooking Indian Curries for many years with excellent results and 'Curry Powder' has never been an ingredient in any curry I've prepared. Curry paste would be a better choice than powder, but like I said in my previous review, there are numerous Indian websites out there with wonderful authentic curries made by roasting and grinding the seeds as needed. It may require a little more effort than opening a jar but the end result is uncomparable. My review was aimed at those who love Indian food and would love the chance to make an authentic curry. However, I think the curry powder is an excellent choice for you...enjoy!

