Not much to add to other positive reviews. One suggestion for those who have access to Middle Eastern grocery -- labne (aka yogurt cheese) works very well in place of whole milk yogurt. It creates a very creamy consistency and never separates as yogurts sometimes can. I just cut back on the quantity a bit (as it's completely drained and thus very intense).

