I've made this dish three times in two weeks! It is truly outstanding! A few suggested changes: I accidentally doubled the cashew quantity. Try it - it's even better. Also, try using cubed chicken breast instead of whole pieces. The cooking time is faster, and the dish is easier to eat with no bones to deal with. Also, if you use 1/2 tsp of cayenne as the recipe indicates, understand that the dish will be very hot. (3 red peppers on the menu of your local Tai restaurant.) 1/3 tsp is about right for me... Lastly, the dish is even more amazing after its had a chance to "get happy" in the 'fridge over night. Try making it the day before and adding the cashews and yogurt before serving.

