Rating: 3
As someone who grew up with authentic curry dishes (being from Fiji originally) I thought this was alright but it isn't the best I've tried. I followed the recipe with minor differences. I used skinless, boneless chicken thighs as that's what I had on hand and normally use in my curry dishes. I didn't have cilantro or cashews but I did use crushed almonds which added a nice texture and taste. Instead of using cayenne, I used red hot chili pepper flakes that I brought back from my last trip to Fiji. These added a real zing to the dish. I also used Patak's Madras curry paste instead of curry powder which also added to the spiciness which I prefer. Overall, this wasn't a bad dish. I think I was just disappointed because of the overhyped ratings. My husband really enjoyed it though but he's a born and bred Canadian so his palate is a little different. I would make this again because it is a tasty dish with basmati rice, mango chutney, and tamarind chutney mixed in, but my butter chicken is way better.

