Rating: 3
This dish was fabulous. I made it with a few modifications, as I'm on Weight Watchers and wanted to reduce the calories a bit. I also decided to experiment by making this in the crockpot, and it worked wonderfully. Here are my modifications: Place butter (1-2 T only) in crock pot, along with onions, garlic, and ginger. Place 3 lbs boneless, skinless chicken breasts (cut into 4 oz portions) on top of onions. Drain the can of tomatoes; place on top of chicken breasts. Cook in crock pot for 7-9 hours on Low. One hour before serving, add yogurt, spices (curry, salt, cumin, cayenne), and cashews. Cook another hour on Low. Serve with rice, garnish with chopped cilantro, and offer a side of mixed yogurt/lemon juice. This turned out fantastic. I think, if I continue to seek low-calorie recipes, I will omit cashews and substitute a bit of cornstarch to thicken the sauce. The cashews didn't add a lot of flavor, but they added a lot of calories and fat. But, overall, I loved this recipe.

