Rating: 4
I made this recipe as written except I used skinless boneless chicken breasts cut into bite-sized pieces. Yes the meat turned out a little dry, but I did this for ease of eating. The curry powder I used is a local blend, made here in Washington, and is quite hot and spicy on its own. I used the correct amount of cayenne and thought the heat just right. One thing I've learned about making curries is that after adding the seasonings, cook until the oil separates out. This fries the seasonings and adds more flavor. You can tell when this happens by looking and listening to your sauce. Also, I believe that this is an Asian curry, not Indian (as noted by the name the cookbook it was adapted from). I froze a portion of this dish after I added the yogurt and cashews and am eager to see how it holds up. I'm a Personal Chef and Restaurant Owner and am adding this to my menus.

