Rating: 4
Of the literally hundreds of things I've made from this site, this is without a doubt in the Top 10. I followed the recipe exactly except with boneless skinless breasts and with strained greek lowfat yogurt (all the dense, creamy richess with half the fat). To those cutting/eliminating either the butter or the cayenne-- DON'T! Butter is an essential part of the taste profile of this dish, and you need the bite of the cayenne to cut the richness of the butter/yogurt/cashews. This recipe as written is by no means 'hot', even for children. This is even better as leftovers, but as the recipe suggests, leave out the yogurt and cashews until reheating. EXTRAORDINARY!

